  "text": "The apparatus was the same as used by [CITATION_1] . During trials, cylindrical plastic food cups (40 mm diameter, 35 mm high) cups were filled with a layer of scented digging medium (20 mm) and one cup was baited with a small piece of cereal (30 mg; Honey Nut Loop, Kellogg). Small pieces of grained bait were mixed with digging media to mask for eventual odor cues.",
